Seventeen miners who weremissing in a copper mine fire were found today and efforts wereunderway to rescue them and 29 others who were trapped but safein an underground lunch room, officials said.    The mine's owner, Noranda Inc. &lt;NOR>, said one miner diedin the fire, six miners escaped unharmed, 29 made it to anunderground lunch room, where they had air and water, and 17were later found safe in other lunch rooms. Reuter&#3;